<div class="blog" style="margin-top: 16%">
<h2>25<sup>th</sup> April 2020</h2>
This is my first blog post. Spent a good part of the day designing the blog. This blog is basically an update indicator for the website, as well as a journal for all my web affairs.
I will not be including anything personal in this.<br>
<a href="https://scratch.mit.edu/users/knitt" >My account</a> was blocked from scratch 3 days ago on the 21<sup>st</sup> of March, for giving my e-mail to a Scratcher: <a href="https://scratch.mit.edu/users/mallikaook" >mallikaook</a>, even though I already knew
her. During that, I started working on the <a href="https://scratch.mit.edu/users/randomsite" >Scratch account</a> for <a href="https://randomsite.github.io" >RandomSite</a>. I had spent a lot of the lockdown
developing that website, when I realized that I had not yet begun to further develop my own website. I still have a long length of lockdown ahead of me: the Coronavirus pandemic does not seem to be slowing down soon,
so I decided to make a movie completely out of text, like my <a href="../charnimation" >CHARnimations</a>. It would be imaginatively titled: "CHARnimation: the movie". After a couple of days however, my
progress was tedious, and I decided to make a blog instead. My movie is still in progress, and should be done by the end of the summer vacation/lockdown. I also remade a song with my friend 
<a href="https://keshuook.github.io" >keshuook</a>, and will be posting it on my scratch page, and possibly this website soon. Aside from the web, I am reading some classics. I am also reading some economics books.
I got a shortwave radio recently, and used to spend some time listening to the news, but it has just gotten too depressing now. I have a lot to do on this site, and will be sure to see you tomorrow.
<br>Goodbye from United Geekdom.
</div>
